Class Array_StringList

java.lang.Object
Abstract_StringList
Array_StringList
All Implemented Interfaces:
StringList
Direct Known Subclasses:
Array_StringList_Op
public class Array_StringList extends Abstract_StringList
Array based list. Implements those methods not already implemented in Abstract_StringList. Also includes items related to the list capacity.
Author:
Kevin Lillis

  • Constructor Details

    • Array_StringList

      public Array_StringList()
      Constructs an empty array-based list with capacity set to the INITIAL_CAPACITY.

    • Array_StringList

      public Array_StringList(String[] eArr)
      Constructs an array-based list containing the elements in the specified array. If the array argument is non-empty, the capacity of this list is set to the list's size. However, if the array argument is empty, the capacity of this list is set to the INITIAL_CAPACITY.
      Parameters:
      eArr - array containing initial list elements
